    Class and Description
    GeometryType 
    MultiThemeParameter 
    ProcessParameter
    This class represents parameters for a generalisation process (algorithm or more complex process).
    ScaleLine 
    ScaleMaster
    A ScaleMaster is a set of scale lines (timelines where time is replaced by scale), inspired from the ScaleMaster of Brewer & Buttenfield (2007, 2009).
    ScaleMasterElement
    A ScaleMasterUnit is the unit part of a scale master: it's what is inside a scale interval, in a scaleline of the ScaleMaster, i.e. a class name from a given DB and a generalisation process along with its parameters.
    ScaleMasterElement.ProcessPriority 
    ScaleMasterEnrichment
    This is the abstract class of the enrichments triggered in a scale master process.
    ScaleMasterGeneProcess 
    ScaleMasterMultiElement 
    ScaleMasterMultiLine 
    ScaleMasterMultiProcess
    ScaleMasterMultiProcess is a specific type of ScaleMaster process that is applied on multiple themes and not only one like the other processes (except the landuse process).
    ScaleMasterTheme
